definition: right/correct/couple/pair/towards/at/for/to face/opposite/to treat (sb a certain way)/to match together/to adjust/to fit/to suit/to answer/to reply/classifier: couple
erhua variant of 不對勁|不对劲[bu4 dui4 jin4]

sentences.english: The soup that I ordered yesterday did not taste as it should.
sentences.chinese: 昨天我叫的湯，味道好像不對勁。

sentences.english: But there seems something wrong in the rugby this year.
sentences.chinese: 但是今年的橄欖球賽好象有點不對勁。

sentences.english: I could sense that there was something wrong. It felt wrong.
sentences.chinese: 我能感覺出一些不對，它不對勁。

sentences.english: But in the past decade, something went horribly wrong.
sentences.chinese: 但在過去十年，事情變得不對勁了。

sentences.english: Once we started questioning her, things didn’t add up.
sentences.chinese: 一旦我們開始詢問她，就發現事情不對勁了。

sentences.english: Nothing smells a rat. I told you that he's an all-right guy.
sentences.chinese: 沒什麼不對勁的，我告訴你他是一個很好的小夥子。

sentences.english: He quickly ran home, looking as if there was something wrong with him.
sentences.chinese: 他快步跑回家，看上去好象有什麼事不對勁。

sentences.english: I don’t want to say he steals them, but I really smell a rat.
sentences.chinese: 雖然我不想說他偷我的書，但我確實覺得不對勁。

sentences.english: If you feel weird about something tell him.
sentences.chinese: 如果你感到有些事情不對勁，那就跟他直說。

sentences.english: However, Hutchinson senses something isn't right.
sentences.chinese: 但是，漢金森感覺到有點不對勁。

sentences.english: But I never got over the feeling that something was wrong.
sentences.chinese: 但我卻從來就沒有擺脫掉那些倍感不對勁的感覺。

sentences.english: Ever since the first time I entered a guy's locker room, I felt different.
sentences.chinese: 我第一次走進男士換衣間時就感覺不對勁。

sentences.english: You and I need to have a conversation.
sentences.chinese: “什麼不對勁？”王一飛不明白這個問題的意思。

sentences.english: She feel very awkward with a needle.
sentences.chinese: 她做針線活時感到很不對勁。

sentences.english: I'm out of order. Peh , you're out of order. This whole courtroom's out of order.
sentences.chinese: 我是不正常，畢，你也不對勁，整個法庭都出毛病了。

sentences.english: Su Yan jump to the children, let children feel wrong.
sentences.chinese: 蘇巖馬躍討好孩子，讓孩子感覺不對勁。

definition: lacking in confidence/diffident/to have a guilty conscience
to overdo it/to overstep the limit/excessively/above one's head/overhead
at a loss to know what to do (idiom); bewildered
to act in a fit of pique/to get in a huff/to be peeved
unimportant/not serious/it doesn't matter/never mind/it looks all right, but
